    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Arches characteristic of Renaissance and later classicizing styles, consisting of a large central opening under a semicircular arch flanked by two smaller rectangular openings. Illustrated in Serlio's 'Architettura' (1537), and considered a characteristic element of Palladian architecture. Named for Veneto architect Andrea Palladio, or in reference to Sebastiano Serlio, who wrote an architectural treatise describing similar arches of ancient Rome.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000018341/Harris, Historic Architecture Sourcebook (1977)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000109602/Gerwing, Palladian window or Serliana (2011)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Architectonisch motief, kenmerkend voor de Renaissance en latere stijlen die de klassieke stijl imiteerden, bestaande uit een grote centrale opening onder een halfronde boog, geflankeerd door twee kleinere, rechthoekige openingen. Weergegeven in ���Architettura' (1537) van Serlio en beschouwd als een kenmerkend element van de Palladiaanse architectuur.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>以文藝復興與之後古典化風格為特色的建築主題，半圓拱下較大開口的兩側附有較小的矩形開口。塞里歐（Serlio）的著作“Architettura”（1537）描繪有塞里歐拱的外觀，此類型拱券被視為帕拉迪奧式建築的典型基本元素。為威尼斯建築師安德里亞•帕拉迪奧（Andrea Palladio）命名，他引用塞巴斯蒂安諾•塞利歐（Sebastiano Serlio）的名字撰寫了一篇建築論文，描述了古羅馬的類似拱門。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000079740/AS-Academia Sinica data (2014-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Architektonisches Motiv, kennzeichnend für die Renaissance und spätere klassizistische Stile; es besteht aus einer großen zentralen Öffnung unter einem halbkreisförmigen Bogen und wird flankiert von zwei kleineren rechteckigen Öffnungen. Abgebildet in Serlios 'Architettura' (1537) wird als kennzeichnendes Element der  palladianischen Architektur angesehen.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>German</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000232/IfM-SMB-PK</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
